QMT MCP — vendored components and local modifications
======================================================

vendor/ contains source from:

    qmt-trade-mcp  (https://github.com/yywx55/qmt-trade-mcp)
    Copyright (c) 2026 田健伸 — MIT License (see vendor/LICENSE)

Local modifications applied to the vendored copy:

1. xttrade_mcp/server.py: fixed an upstream typo `xtttrader` -> `xttrader`
   (in init_trader and _make_account). As shipped upstream this typo makes
   EVERY trade tool — including all read-only query_* tools — fail with an
   ImportError, because _make_account cannot build an account object.

The launcher (qmt_mcp.py) is original and:
  * exposes all xtdata tools,
  * exposes ONLY the read-only query_* tools from xttrade (all order/cancel/
    transfer/borrow/export and lifecycle/callback/subscribe tools removed),
  * adds Bearer-token auth,
  * drives the trader start/connect handshake in the background.
